30yrs old . Just getting into investing with stocks and such. Already max Roth (started mid 20s). Have 1 year+ emergency fund(more like 4-5yrs). I have 8k I want to invest. Its the start of my investing so I am mostly looking for long term, retirement.  Dont need this money in near future. No debts. I don’t know why I never really started investing my extra funds But with recent news of market due to virus I was thinking I could start.  Especially since I’m thinking longer term... better to just start and get into it ASAP. Using E*trade

So most would go in an ETF while spending 30-40% in stocks, With the 8k. Thoughts? 

I was thinking for an ETF to go for - VTI

How many stocks would you recommend I going for.  2-4? 

Stocks I've looked into and am thinking to invest in would be:
* MFST
* TER
* ISRG
* WM
* CMCSA
* COST
* LVMH
* BABA

Any suggestions and advice would be great. Is now really fine time to enter? Should I spend the 8k over time instead of all at once?
Thank you
